dance_style: bachata, cha cha, dance, merengue, salsa
description:
We are excited to bring you dancing the 2nd Saturday of every month right in the heart of downtown, with a wooden dance floor!!!!! 8:15pm Doors open
Salsa Caliente’s team will be there to greet you. 8:30pm Salsa lesson
Taught by World Salsa University certified instructor, Christina Morrison. No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson so you will already know a LOT of people by the time the dancing begins. 9:30pm- midnight
Dancing to Salsa, Bachata, Merengue, Cha Cha Cha and more. Ages 16+ welcome. CASH ONLY at the door. $15.00 per person. Tickets available at the door or on Eventbrite. There will be a small non-alcoholic concession available as a fundraiser for the teams. *Limited capacity. First come first served. We reserve the right to refuse entrance at the door.

event_name: Sunday Sundown Social: Salsa Fire, Bachata Desire, Kizomba Inspire
description: Join us for a vibrant late afternoon of Latin dancing by the ocean! We’ll begin with a beginner-friendly lesson— no partner or experience needed. After the class, enjoy an open-air social featuring a dynamic blend of Salsa, Bachata, and Kizomba, with just a light touch of Merengue to round out the evening. Schedule: 3:45 PM – Doors Open, 4:00 – 4:30 PM – Intro to Kizomba, 4:30 – 7:30 PM – Social Dancing. This is a beautiful, inclusive, and supportive community where new friendships are made and everyone belongs.
location: Songhees Plaza (near the Johnson Street Bridge), Victoria, British Columbia
price: $5 for students (with valid ID), $10 general admission

event_name: West Coast Swing in the Park!
description: Come join us for another evening of fun and WCS dancing in Beacon Hill Park! WCS music will be provided by DJ Carolyn. For those who are familiar with the routine, the 2018 WCS Rally Song will be played at 6:30, 7:30 and 8:30pm. Sam Jackson and Meaghan Efford, from wcsmovementmethods.com will be on hand to answer questions about WCS or how to improve your WCS dancing. They will also demo some incredible WCS dancing at 7pm.
location: Cameron Bandshell @ Beacon Hill Park Victoria, British Columbia

description: Recurring weekly West Coast Swing social dance every Saturday. Doors open at 6:45 pm, lesson at 7:00 pm, social dance 8:00–11:00 pm. $10 ($5 for students). No experience or partner required.
location: BC Swing Dance Club Victoria, Victoria, BC
